Description:
RENOVATED LIFESTYLE APARTMENT IN BOUTIQUE BLOCK
Comfort and charm are on offer here with this fully renovated top floor apartment on the fringe of the Melbourne CBD.
- 1 large bedroom with built in robes
- Oversized living room
- Renovated kitchen with washing machine
- Well-appointed bathroom
- Polished timber floors
- Secure off-street parking
- Split system reverse cycle heating/cooling and instantaneous hot water
This tastefully renovated apartment nestled quietly in a 1970s built block presents both comfort and convenience. Only moments from the Melbourne CBD, main travel routes, parks and shops. Purchase as an investment or a primary residence...You win either way.
Conditions of entry - IDENTIFICATION and contact number required, otherwise entry may be refused.
The information about this property has been supplied to us by the property owner, while we have no cause to doubt its accuracy, we provide no guarantee. We cannot attest to the functionality of any fixtures, fittings or inclusions to the property. Land and apartment dimensions and floor/site plans are supplied by third parties. Typing mistakes, omissions, transposing can occur, we provide to assist but make no representation. Buyers must carry out their own due diligence.

Description:
Stunning Milieu apartment in the heart of Collingwood
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
A showcase of bespoke contemporary elegance and cutting-edge industrial style, this stunning apartment has been cleverly crafted for effortless luxury by renowned architects, DKO. It enjoys a coveted Collingwood address on the corner of Wellington Street, just a short stroll to Peel Street cafes, vibrant Smith Street and city trams. Perched on Level Three of 'Peel by Milieu', above the award-winning Congress restaurant, it has been designed to maximise the glorious north aspect with a large open plan living and dining area offering district views, and covered balcony with bench seating. At the heart of the apartment is a sleek gourmet gas kitchen with premium Smeg appliances including a dishwasher, a breakfast bar and custom cabinetry. Nearby is a bright main bedroom with built-ins and a smart ensuite, second bedroom also with built-ins, and stylish bathroom. It features a European laundry, ducted a/c, surround sound, exposed concrete ceilings complemented by hardwood floors, full height doors, muted neutral tones plus a basement car space with storage. The impeccably maintained building provides video intercom security, lift access and bike storage.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Stunning Boutique Warehouse Apartment-1 of only 4
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
An abundance of natural light welcomes you to your inner city oasis-high ceilings, exposed beams and brickwork, original wooden floorboards means this is a true Collingwood warehouse apartment. Step straight into open plan living with an entertainer's kitchen; mirrored splashback, 6 burner Smeg cooktop with an extra wide oven underneath, and a central island bench that accommodates bar seating for your friends to perch and imbibe whilst you man the pans! Then move into the separate dining area that opens up into the oversized, light filled terrace. A generous bathroom and laundry with masses of storage, shower over bath, BIR is both bedrooms complete this incredible space. In addition to being located within a stone's through of public transport and the city, 2 parking permits are conveniently available for you and your guests. If you have had enough of cookie cutter apartments, or if you thought you had to compromise between living in the inner city and having an outdoor space you absolutely must inspect this property. An extraordinary opportunity to enjoy the conveniences of a Collingwood lifestyle in an exclusive, low density block.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Sophisticated Style in the Heart of Cosmopolitan Collingwood
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
With its intelligent design, premium features and prime position in Collingwood's bustling Foy & Gibson precinct, this brilliant third-floor Oxley abode is a perfect choice for inner-city professionals and blue-chip investors alike. Stylish and serene, the apartment's immediately impressive interior boasts a spacious bedroom with built-in robes, together with a large dedicated study and sleek central bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiling. Adding to its appeal is a versatile open-plan living/meals area leading out to a wide balcony, along with a superb stone-bench kitchen complete with stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Flanked by floor-to-ceiling windows for an abundance of light, the apartment also includes split-system heating and cooling, laundry facilities, plus lift to secure foyer, lower-level car space and storage cage, as well as exclusive residents' rooftop terrace and swimming pool. Previously returning an average of $48K per annum as a short-stay rental property, the very best of Collingwood and Fitzroy is at your fingertips including Smith Street's boutique shops and major supermarkets, cool cafes and renowned restaurants, as well as trams to hospital precincts and the CBD.

If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Superb warehouse conversion, iconic city-fringe setting
Once a hive of activity in Foy & Gibson's illustrious retail heyday, now a spacious oasis of modern living; this superb apartment is a model of Melbourne's post-industrial evolution made for an exciting city-fringe lifestyle. Whitewashed extra-thick brickwork, polished hardwood floorboards, a broad bank of windows to Little Oxford Street and an historic barn door all add iconic character to the brilliant design of this impressively-proportioned warehouse conversion. Set quietly to the rear on the second floor, this light-filled apartment extends over 140 sqms (approx.) and also includes a secure car space on title. Located at Collingwood's vibrant heart, the secluded space is both an outstanding single-level sanctuary and a handy springboard to nearby Smith/Brunswick/Gertrude Streets, trams, East Melbourne hospitals, the city and elegant local parks and gardens. Have a poke around the area and get hooked on a daily discovery of fabulous cafes, restaurants, specialty shops and galleries. Immaculately presented with Nobo heating, LED lighting and new carpets, this striking home features wide entrance hallway with in-built storage cupboards, 2 huge bedrooms with mirror BIRs, central bathroom, laundry, large kitchen with brand new stainless-steel appliances and a substantial open-plan living and dining room. Be a part of history in an exceptional contemporary context and make this sensational warehouse conversion an essential part of your new life.

Description:
A secluded, spacious and inspiring recipe for success
Drive directly in off Little Oxford Street to this sensational warehouse conversion that sates the appetite with its light-filled space, spectacular courtyard and superb kitchen which has been given the nod of approval by MoVidas' owner and acclaimed chef Frank Camorra. The exhilarating flavours of an enticing city-fringe lifestyle combine with imagination, precision and joie de vivre in this stunning 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment. The historic Foy & Gibson precinct is synonymous with inner-Melbourne's best warehouse living and this secluded sanctuary at the heart of Collingwood is one of its most impressive. So, rev up the Vespa, cycle or walk as there's so much to explore right outside the door. Secure single-level access via intercom entrance and rear remote-control roller door with a wrought-iron gate provide an effortless entree to the light and airy interior staged over 2 easily-negotiated levels. Overlooking a vibrant alfresco terrace and lush vertical garden (automated irrigation), the ground-floor living and dining zone with high ceiling incorporates the main bedroom (WIR and ensuite), laundry and, with an award-winning celebrity chef in the family, a luxury designer kitchen boasting Smeg Victoria cooker, Miele dishwasher, plumbed coffee station, copious self-close storage and dream pantry. Up a short flight of stairs, the second level features free-flowing retreat and study areas, 2 further bedrooms, indulging bathroom with dual clawfoot baths plus walkway to the undercover car space. Including all the ingredients for inner-city success such as heating and cooling, storerooms/cellar, rich hardwood floors, LED lights, thick brick walls and original steel beams; this outstanding warehouse apartment is one to savour close to Smith/Gertrude Streets' cafes, restaurants and shops, galleries, trams, East Melbourne hospitals and Fitzroy Gardens.

Description:
Much loved c1920s family home with outstanding potential!
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Travel back to the 1920s with this much loved home set in the historic heart of Collingwood. Owned by just one family and offered for the first time, it presents an outstanding opportunity to renovate and create your dream residence (STCA). In addition, it is ideally placed strolling distance to Smith Street cafes, city trams and Victoria Park station, and provides easy access to Hoddle Street. Beyond its gabled stucco facade, the existing floorplan comprises an entrance hall leading to a huge front bedroom and good sized second bedroom. Further on is a spacious central living room with gas heating, an adjacent dining room, original gas kitchen and bathroom with a shower over a freestanding bath and separate w/c. Outside is a low maintenance backyard with side access. It features a separate internal laundry, store room, high ceilings, leadlight windows, ornate mantels and gas hot water.

If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. If you've been searching for that modern lifestyle in the perfect location, then this is it!

A striking warehouse home
Sold by Michael Amarant (Jellis Craig Fitzroy) 0411 144 569
This striking two bedroom apartment, part of the Foy & Gibson complex makes a glamorous warehouse home. Exposed brick and steel highlights speak of this apartment's industrial heritage while soaring leadlight windows, timber floors and unique curved doors add further warmth and character in an open living domain that defines living and dining via a clever split level design. The inspired kitchen features s/steel appliances, shelving and counters that add a commercial element to the space contrasting against black tiled splashbacks. Bedrooms share a neat central bathroom that along with heating, ceiling fans, Euro laundry, built-in robes, secure entry and car space, puts you at the heart of the inner city. Metres to Smith Street cafes, restaurants and trams and a short stroll to the CBD.

Description:
PROPERTY UNDER OFFER
*** This property is available for Inspection by Appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST - CLOSING 27 APRIL AT 5PM (IF NOT SOLD PRIOR)
Landmark conversion in a prized Collingwood locale
Boasting a blue ribbon Collingwood address, this landmark abode has been transformed by Folk Architects from a heritage lolly factory into a stunning three-level home. Featured in Inside Out Magazine and The Design Files, the custom conversion is defined by luxuriously appointed interiors with retained industrial character and alfresco entertaining areas. It is located strolling distance to Smith Street cafes, Victoria Park station and city trams. The iconic facade reveals a wide foyer with timber floors, large front bedroom with extensive built-ins and plush twin bathroom. Drenched in light at the back is a huge living and dining area with soaring raked ceilings and featuring the original pipework, plus a gourmet kitchen offering stainless steel European gas appliances and a terrazzo island bench. Beyond French doors is a private leafy courtyard with bench seating, or potential car space with ROW access. A pink perforated steel staircase leads to a deluxe atrium-style master bedroom with built-ins and a superb balcony enjoying district views, generous second bedroom with built-ins, bright twin terrazzo bathroom with a bath and floor heating, and glorious entertaining terrace in tranquil surrounds. It also has a separate laundry, understair storage, split system a/c, hydronic heating and exposed brick walls.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Eclectic and totally unique, this striking warehouse conversion, true to its industrial heritage presents sophisticated living in the heart of Collingwood. Concrete floors and soaring exposed trusses frame industrial chic interiors where a cube incorporating storage and mezzanine bedroom can be moved freely in a space that has the versatility to be changed seasonally.
